Police Minister Bheki Cele is today releasing the third-quarter crime statistics. This relates to crimes committed between the first of July to the end of September when the country moved to level 2 and then level 1 of the lockdown. • Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. JOHANNESBURG - Police Minister Bheki Cele is expected to present the quarterly crime statistics on Friday. It will give a picture of crime in the country between July and September. READ: Cele: Decrease in crime from April to June This was when the country was moving from a hard lockdown to eased restrictions. In August, Cele announced gender-based violence had dropped between April and June.